Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Chapter 4  -  Section 4.4", "Title"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "I",
  StyleBox["n this ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" notebook, you will explore the behavior of a complex solution to \
a nonhomogeneous higher order linear differential equation.",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "\n\n",
  StyleBox["In most cases, to adapt this code to other problems, you will \
have to change only the input shown in red. To open a cell grouping, \
double-click on the right-hand side of the double cell marker.",
    FontSize->14]
}], "Subsubtitle"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Problem 11:  y''' - y'' + y' - y = sec(t) \t\t\
\>", "Section"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving the Differential Equation (not so easy)", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
We will begin by solving the differential equation by the method of variation \
of parameters. We must first find the fundamental set of solutions.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(r\^3 - r\^2 + r - 1\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "\[Equal]", "0"}], ",", "r"}], 
      "]"}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
We will define our solnvector using the fundamental solutions based on the \
above values of r. This will provide us with an easy way to compute the array \
whose determinant is needed for the Wronskian. This array is a matrix and is \
defined as a list of lists. The last expression shows the array in the more \
typical form.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{\(solnvector[t_]\), "=", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
        StyleBox[\(\[ExponentialE]\^t, Sin[t], Cos[t]\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
        "}"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(wrarray = {solnvector[
            t], \(solnvector'\)[t], \(solnvector''\)[t]} // 
        Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(% // MatrixForm\)}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
To arrive at the determinants in the numerator of the integrals, we can copy \
and paste from the Wronskian array, and then change the appropriate terms.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"w1array", "=", 
        StyleBox[\({{0, Sin[t], Cos[t]}, {0, 
              Cos[t], \(-Sin[t]\)}, {1, \(-Sin[t]\), \(-Cos[t]\)}}\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], 
      StyleBox[";",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"w2array", "=", 
        StyleBox[\({{\[ExponentialE]\^t, 0, Cos[t]}, {\[ExponentialE]\^t, 
              0, \(-Sin[t]\)}, {\[ExponentialE]\^t, 1, \(-Cos[t]\)}}\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], 
      StyleBox[";",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"w3array", "=", 
        StyleBox[\({{\[ExponentialE]\^t, Sin[t], 0}, {\[ExponentialE]\^t, 
              Cos[t], 0}, {\[ExponentialE]\^t, \(-Sin[t]\), 1}}\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], 
      StyleBox[";",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(wr = 
      Det[wrarray] // Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(w1 = 
      Det[w1array] // Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(w2 = 
      Det[w2array] // Simplify\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(w3 = 
      Det[w3array] // Simplify\)}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
We can now construct the solution using formula 12 in your text.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "=", 
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(e\^\(\(t\)\(\ \)\)\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 
            0]], \(\[Integral]\_0\%t\(\( Sec[
                      t]\ w1\)\/wr\) \[DifferentialD]t\)}], "+", 
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(Sin[t]\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          " ", \(\[Integral]\_0\%t\(\( Sec[
                      t]\ w2\)\/wr\) \[DifferentialD]t\)}], "+", 
        RowBox[{
          StyleBox[\(Cos[t]\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox[" ",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 
            0]], \(\[Integral]\_0\%t\(\( Sec[
                      t]\ w3\)\/wr\) \[DifferentialD]t\)}]}]}]], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "The formula looks innocent enough, but the one of the integrals (the first \
one) is not at all trivial! In fact, this integral involves complex functions \
that are well documented and even have names. What would happen if we use the \
",
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command?"
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[y, t, eq, soln]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"eq", "=", 
        StyleBox[\(\(y'''\)[t] - \(y''\)[t] + \(y'\)[t] - y[t] \[Equal] 
            Sec[t]\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"soln", "=", 
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"DSolve", "[", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"eq", ",", 
                RowBox[{\(y[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox["2",
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ",", 
                RowBox[{\(\(y'\)[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox[\(-1\),
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ",", 
                RowBox[{\(\(y''\)[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox["1",
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}]}], "}"}], ",", \(y[t]\), 
            ",", "t"}], "]"}], "//", "Simplify"}]}]}], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Analyzing the Solution Graphically", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
We will begin by plotting the solution over a small domain and gradually \
enlarge the domain. \
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
        RowBox[{\(y[t] /. soln\), ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"t", ",", "0", ",", 
              StyleBox["1",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
      ";"}]], "Input"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
        RowBox[{\(y[t] /. soln\), ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"t", ",", "0", ",", 
              StyleBox["2",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
      ";"}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
It appears as though the solution is not defined when t gets larger than \
about 1.5.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
        RowBox[{\(y[t] /. soln\), ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"t", ",", "0", ",", 
              StyleBox["1.5",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
      ";"}]], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Taking Another Look at the Solution", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We could try to look at the numerical solution to this differential \
equation using the ",
  StyleBox["NDSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command"
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"numsoln", "=", 
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"NDSolve", "[", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"eq", ",", 
                RowBox[{\(y[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox["2",
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ",", 
                RowBox[{\(\(y'\)[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox[\(-1\),
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ",", 
                RowBox[{\(\(y''\)[0]\), "\[Equal]", 
                  StyleBox["1",
                    FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}]}], "}"}], ",", \(y[t]\), 
            ",", \({t, 0, 10}\)}], "]"}], "//", "Simplify"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
This doesn't help much, since it cannot seem to get much past t=1.5  either. \
Let us explore the analytical solution arrived at earlier.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[ysoln]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(ysoln[t_] = 
      y[t] /. soln\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "[", 
      StyleBox["1.",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "[", 
      StyleBox["1.5",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "[", 
      StyleBox["1.7",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "[", 
      StyleBox["2.",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"ysoln", "[", 
      StyleBox["3.",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}]}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
You will notice that we are getting answers for larger values of t, but the \
answers are complex numbers. For smaller values of t, the imaginary parts are \
essentially 0.\
\>", "Text"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
